!! Plugin files

|!File |!Type |!Role |
|`plugin.info` |metadata |Plugin metadata |
|`routes/upload.js` |`route` |`POST /api/file-upload` &mdash; receive base64 file, write to `/files/`, run thumbnail processor |
|`routes/rename.js` |`route` |`POST /api/file-rename` &mdash; rename file on disk (incl. `_generated/`) |
|`routes/delete.js` |`route` |`POST /api/file-delete` &mdash; delete file from disk (incl. `_generated/`) |
|`widgets/dropzone.js` |`widget` |`<$file-dropzone>` &mdash; extends core dropzone, uploads via XHR |
|`startup.js` |`startup` |Browser-side: registers `th-saving-tiddler` and `th-deleting-tiddler` hooks |
|`settings.tid` |UI |Control Panel &rarr; Settings &rarr; File Upload (thumbnails, media types, dedup) |
|`cascade-thumbnail.tid` |cascade |ViewTemplateBodyFilter &mdash; routes to thumbnail body template |
|`body-thumbnail.tid` |template |Body template: thumbnail with click-to-expand |
|`toolbar-version-switch.tid` |toolbar |ViewToolbar button: toggle thumbnail/full-size |
|`toolbar-version-switch-visibility.tid` |config |Makes toolbar button visible by default |
|`icon-expand.tid` |icon |Expand SVG icon |
|`icon-shrink.tid` |icon |Shrink SVG icon |
|`styles-thumbnail.tid` |stylesheet |CSS for thumbnail wrapper, full-view embed sizing |
|`readme.tid` |doc |Plugin readme |

!! Wiki config tiddlers

These live in the wiki's tiddler store. `media-types` is bundled as a shadow tiddler with the plugin (default whitelist). Others are created via the settings UI or manually. All are read per request (no restart needed).

|!Tiddler |!Type |!Role |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/media-types` |JSON array |Allowed MIME types for upload |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/thumb-images` |`yes`/`no` |Enable image thumbnail generation |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/thumb-pdfs` |`yes`/`no` |Enable PDF thumbnail generation |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/thumb-resolution` |string |Thumbnail max dimension (e.g. `200` or `300x200`) |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/thumb-rendering` |`yes`/`no` |Show thumbnails by default |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/global-dedup` |`yes`/`no` |Global content-hash deduplication |

!! Restart rules

|!Change |!Restart needed? |
|Edit wiki config tiddlers (media-types, thumb-*, global-dedup) |No &mdash; read from `$tw.wiki` per request |
|Edit `runner-actions.json` |No for upload.js (reads per request) &mdash; Yes for runner plugin |
|Edit `.tid` files (settings, styles, templates) |No &mdash; plugin tiddlers reload on restart, but config changes via UI take effect immediately |
|Edit any `.js` module |Yes &mdash; JS modules load at boot |

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="tip">
<$fill $name="body">
On Windows, use `taskkill //F //PID <pid> //T` to kill the server before restarting.
</$fill>
</$transclude>

!! API reference

!!! POST /api/file-upload

Request:
```json
{
  "filename": "photo.jpg",
  "type": "image/jpeg",
  "content": "<base64>",
  "targetPath": "images/photo.jpg"
}
```

Response (200):
```json
{
  "canonicalUri": "/files/images/photo.jpg",
  "filename": "photo.jpg",
  "generatedUri": "/files/images/_generated/photo_thumb.jpg"
}
```

|!Status |!Meaning |
|200 |File uploaded successfully |
|400 |Missing fields or invalid JSON |
|403 |Path traversal detected |
|413 |Upload too large (>50MB JSON) |
|415 |MIME type not in whitelist |

!!! POST /api/file-rename

Request:
```json
{"oldUri": "/files/images/old.jpg", "newUri": "/files/images/new.jpg"}
```

|!Status |!Meaning |
|200 |File renamed, returns `{newCanonicalUri}` |
|404 |Source file not found |
|409 |Target file already exists |

!!! POST /api/file-delete

Request:
```json
{"uri": "/files/images/photo.jpg"}
```

|!Status |!Meaning |
|200 |File deleted, returns `{deleted: true}` |
|404 |File not found |

!! Configuration

!!! Media types

Edit `$:/config/rimir/file-upload/media-types` (JSON array) to add or remove allowed MIME types. Changes take effect immediately (no restart needed).

!!! File path routing

Target paths under `/files/` are computed by the `<$file-dropzone>` widget using built-in routing logic (first match wins):

# If `subfolder` attribute is set on the widget &rarr; `<subfolder>/<filename>`
# If `prop-upload-folder` attribute is set &rarr; `<upload-folder>/<filename>`
# If MIME type starts with `image/` &rarr; `images/<filename>`
# If MIME type is `application/pdf` &rarr; `pdf/<filename>`
# Fallback: just `<filename>` (root of `/files/`)

!!! Thumbnails

Controlled via Settings UI (Control Panel &rarr; Settings &rarr; File Upload) or config tiddlers:

|!Tiddler |!Default |!Purpose |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/thumb-images` |`no` |Generate thumbnails for images |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/thumb-pdfs` |`no` |Generate PDF first-page thumbnails (requires Ghostscript) |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/thumb-resolution` |`200` |Max dimension: `200` (single) or `300x200` (WxH) |
|`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/thumb-rendering` |`no` |Show thumbnails instead of full-size by default |

Thumbnail generation uses ImageMagick via `runner-actions.json`:

* `thumb-image`: `magick {{input}} -thumbnail "{{resolution}}>" {{output}}`
* `thumb-pdf`: `magick {{input}}[0] -thumbnail "{{resolution}}>" {{output}}` (first page &rarr; PNG)

Generated files go to `_generated/<basename>_thumb.<ext>` alongside the original.

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="warning">
<$fill $name="body">
PDF thumbnails require both ImageMagick and Ghostscript on the server's `PATH`. ImageMagick delegates PDF rasterisation to Ghostscript automatically (`gs` on Linux, `gswin64c` on Windows).
</$fill>
</$transclude>

!!! Deduplication

`$:/config/rimir/file-upload/global-dedup` (`yes`/`no`) &mdash; when enabled, the widget computes a content hash before upload and skips if an identical file already exists.

!! Widget reference

!!! `<$file-dropzone>`

|!Attribute |!Description |
|`actions` |Action string executed on upload completion |
|`subfolder` |Optional subfolder override (bypasses built-in routing) |
|`prop-*` |Extra fields passed through as action variables |

Action variables available in `actions`:

|!Variable |!Description |
|`<<data>>` |Raw JSON response body |
|`<<type>>` |MIME type of uploaded file |
|`<<filename>>` |Original filename |
|`<<content-hash>>` |Content hash (8-char hex) |
|`<<canonical-uri>>` |Canonical URI of uploaded file (e.g. `/files/images/photo.jpg`) |
|`<<generated-uri>>` |Thumbnail URI if processor ran (e.g. `/files/images/_generated/photo_thumb.jpg`), empty otherwise |

</$fill>
</$transclude>